column15: Description

On every UCLA students' bucketlist- Miles of steam tunnels underneath the campus. Maintenance has been sealing off entrances, but you can still find some around. Destinations to visit include the YRL underground library, Macgowan prop room, Chem lab storage, Pauley, Underground bridge
Find your way in and enjoy a view from one of UCLA's most iconic buildings. Flashlight recommended.
If you're lucky and the door's unlocked, you'll have to squeeze up a narrow ladder and walk on sketchy planks to get here. Great for study breaks.
Nestled in UCLA's south-east corner, it's a peaceful area to eat lunch, catch up with a friend, or just chill by yourself. Contains turtles, bamboo, and benches.
Look around the top level of Parking Lot 3 and you'll find this chill spot with a clear view of downtown. Best for night
Art and history exhibits. Courtyard is a good place to get away and chill
